name: #02_GOD_VALKYRIE
description: In Norse mythology, a valkyrie (from Old Norse valkyrja, "chooser of the slain") is one of a host of female figures who choose those who may die in battle and those who may live. Selecting among half of those who die in battle go to Fólkvangr, Freyjas afterlife, the other half go to the god Odin's hall called Valhalla.
